Draghi: Governing Council is firm in necessity of reaching inflation objective without undue delay
Draghi: Our line of communication today was unanimous https://t.co/mxEosvaLyh
Draghi: Communication is a two-way affair. It is very hard to put the blame of some disappointment on one side only
Draghi: All inflation expectation measures have declined and their correlation with current inflation and oil prices have increased
Draghi: Fiscal consolidation should be growth-friendly
Draghi: Questionnaire was not an initiative that would push banks to deal with NPLs urgently, and we know it takes a long time
Draghi: NPL questionnaire was sent to several banks in several countries
Draghi: Purpose of NPL questionnaire was to gather best practices in governance of NPLs
Draghi: No new unexpected provisioning or new unexpected request for more capital will be made by the supervisor
Draghi: If oil price changes were a short term effect we would look through, but it is not our experiece
Draghi: The best answer to recent developments in financial markets is to make sure that the banking sector is resilient
Draghi: The best answer to stability of financial sector is to make sure that the overall economy returns to sustainable growth
Draghi: Our mandate is price stability, not to protect banks' and insurers' profitability
Draghi: We will review and possibly reconsider our monetary policy in March
Draghi: We confirm our determination to comply with our mandate, even more so in face of adverse developments
Draghi: Circumstances have changed considerably since cut off date of previous projections
Draghi: Measures since June 2014 have been quite effective in improving the financial conditions and the real economy
Draghi: Fiscal policies should support the economic recovery, while remaining in compliance with the fiscal rules of the European Union
Draghi: In order to reap the full benefits from our monetary policy measures, other policy areas must contribute decisively
Draghi: Work will be carried out for the full range of policy options to be available for implementation, if needed
Draghi: It will be necessary to review and possibly reconsider our monetary policy stance at our next meeting in early March
Draghi: In this environment, euro area inflation dynamics also continue to be weaker than expected
Draghi: Downside risks have increased amid heightened uncertainty about EM growth, volatility, geopolitical risk
Draghi: Monetary policy measures that we have adopted since mid-2014 are working
Draghi: Asset purchases are proceeding smoothly and continue to have a favourable impact on the cost and availability of credit
Draghi: We expect rates to remain at present or lower levels for an extended period of time
